---
id: org.dxos.plugin.inbox
name: InboxPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

Unified inbox plugin for `DXOS` Composer — email, calendar, and contacts in one place, surfaced alongside workspace content. Mail syncs from multiple providers (Google/Gmail and JMAP, e.g. Fastmail) into an append-only feed; calendar and contacts sync from Google. AI extractors and a fact-enrichment pass derive structured objects and RDF facts from message content.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.
Each extension is defined in the Appendix or resolved via its URI.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`        |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`        |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`        |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`   |
| `service`   | `org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0`     |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`          |

## External types

Sync and credentials are owned by `@dxos/plugin-connector`; the inbox binds to them rather than
defining its own integration type:

- `Connection` — holds provider credentials (an `AccessToken` Ref). Sourced by send/create ops.
- `SyncBinding` — a relation whose `source` is a `Connection` and whose `target` is the object being
  synced (a Mailbox or Calendar). Carries the durable sync `Cursor`. Sync ops bind to it.

`Feed`, `Message`, `Event`, `Person`, `Tag`, and `TagIndex` are `@dxos/echo` / `@dxos/types` /
`@dxos/schema` types. `Fact` and the `FactStore` come from `@dxos/pipeline-rdf`.

## Types

```mdl
type MessageState
  literals: none | archived | deleted | spam
  # Implemented as a numeric enum (none=0, archived=1, deleted=2, spam=3); slated to become labels.
```

```mdl
type Filter
  desc: A saved, named query filter (as in MailboxArticle.activeFilter), NOT a MessageFilter below.
  fields:
    name: string
    filter: string              # query expression
```

```mdl
type MessageFilter
  desc: |
    An exclusion rule applied across the mailbox UI, sync, and analysis — a matching message is
    hidden and never committed/enriched. Kept intentionally small (currently sender-only); expected
    to grow. Actual code name is also `Filter` (`Mailbox.ts`) — a real naming collision with the
    saved-query `Filter` above, disambiguated here as `MessageFilter`.
  fields:
    from?: string                # case-insensitive regex matched against the sender email
```

```mdl
type Mailbox
  desc: |
    Feed-backed mailbox. Messages are immutable Queue items in the feed, so their tag associations
    and extraction provenance cannot live on the messages themselves — they live on the mutable
    Mailbox in a child TagIndex and the `extracted` map.
  fields:
    name?: string
    feed: Ref<Feed>             # append-only Message stream
    tags: Ref<TagIndex>         # inverse index: tag uri → message ids (labels/hues live on Tag objects)
    extractors?:
      enabled: string[]
      threshold: number         # 0..1 — AI confidence cutoff
    messageFilters?: MessageFilter[]
    instructions?: Ref<Instructions>  # per-mailbox reply guidance; shared or mailbox-specific; the
                                      # reply generator merges its text + skills into the session prompt
    extracted?: Map<string, string[]>  # messageId → ids of objects extracted from it (provenance)
    filters: Filter[]
  note: |
    Provider folders/labels map to Tag objects carrying a foreign key: Gmail labels under
    `com.google.gmail.label`, JMAP mailboxes under `org.ietf.jmap.mailbox`. "Provider" tags have such
    a key; "user" tags do not.
```

```mdl
type Calendar
  fields:
    name?: string
    feed: Ref<Feed>             # append-only stream of synced (Google) Events
    tags: Ref<TagIndex>         # inverse index for immutable feed Events (e.g. the "starred" tag)
```

```mdl
type DraftMessage
  desc: A local (unsent) email. Not a distinct schema — a Message marked as a draft.
  fields:
    marker: properties.mailbox is a valid DXN string  # synced mail never sets this
    subject?: string
    to?: string
    body?: string
    replyTo?: Ref<Message>
```

```mdl
# Draft events are the calendar analogue of an email DraftMessage: locally-created Events that
# have not been pushed to Google. They live in the space db (not the calendar feed), are parented to
# their Calendar, and carry no Google foreign key (synced feed Events do). Edited offline, overlaid on
# the calendar, and pushed to Google on save.
type DraftEvent = Event       # an Event with no google.com foreign key, parented to a Calendar
```

```mdl
type Starred
  desc: |
    A well-known "starred" Tag (foreign key `{ source: 'org.dxos.tag', id: 'starred' }`, from the
    canonical SystemTag registry — see `SystemTags.ts`) applied to feed Messages or Events via the
    container's TagIndex. Deduped by identity so every starring site resolves the same Tag.
    NOTE: `starred` is one of ~10 canonical system tags in that registry (inbox, important, sent,
    draft, personal, social, promotions, updates, forums); this spec documents only the starring one.
```

```mdl
type Settings
  fields:
    conversations?: boolean     # group messages by conversation; show most recent per thread
    loadRemoteImages?: boolean  # render remote (http/https) images inline; off by default (anti-tracking)
```

## Components

```mdl
component MailboxArticle
  desc: Inbox surface for a Mailbox — filterable message list with reading pane.
  props:
    subject: Mailbox
    settings: Settings
  state:
    selected?: Message
    activeFilter?: Filter
  slots:
    toolbar?: ReactNode         # sync / compose / filter actions
  actions:
    selectMessage(message: Message)
    applyFilter(filter: Filter)
    compose()
    reply(message: Message)
    archive(message: Message)
    star(message: Message)
  emits:
    onOpenContact(actor: Actor)
  layout: |
    ┌──────────────┬─────────────────────────┐
    │ [toolbar]    │                         │
    ├──────────────┤                         │
    │ filter chips │  reading pane           │
    │              │                         │
    │ message list │  (selected message      │
    │              │   + related contacts /  │
    │              │   events / threads)     │
    │              │                         │
    └──────────────┴─────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component MessageArticle
  desc: |
    Reading pane for a single Message, shown as the companion to a MailboxArticle (or standalone
    when navigated directly). Renders the message body (HtmlViewer / MarkdownViewer, honoring
    settings.loadRemoteImages) and, alongside it, related contacts / events / thread messages.
  props:
    subject: Message
    companionTo?: Mailbox
```

```mdl
component MailboxFactsCompanion
  desc: |
    Companion surface off a Mailbox article that renders the RDF facts extracted by op:analyzeMailbox.
    Reads the shared per-space FactStore and passes the mailbox's facts to a FactViewer. Phase 1 reads
    once; live streaming into the viewer as enrichment runs is a follow-up.
  props:
    mailbox: Mailbox
```

```mdl
component CalendarArticle
  desc: |
    Day/week view of a Calendar. Overlays synced (feed) Events and draft (local) Events on the
    grid and event list. Toolbar (toolbar idiom) offers "Create event" and, when any draft events
    exist, "Save events to calendar" (disabled unless a Connection targets the Calendar). The
    toolbar also slots the connect/sync action (InitializeCalendarAction): "Connect" auth Surface
    when no Connection targets the Calendar, pull-sync button when one does. Selecting an event in
    the list scrolls its date into view on the month grid (CalendarController.scrollTo).
  props:
    subject: Calendar
  state:
    selected?: Event
    selectedDate?: Date          # default date for newly created events
    range: { from: Date; to: Date }
  actions:
    selectEvent(event: Event)    # selects, opens companion, and scrolls the grid to the event date
    createEvent()                # creates a draft Event (db, parented to Calendar) and focuses it
    syncDraft()             # op:syncDraftEvents (spaceId-scoped) for all draft events on this Calendar
    sync()
```

```mdl
component EventArticle
  desc: |
    Event detail (companion to a Calendar). When the event is draft the header is an editable form
    (title · all-day toggle · start · end-or-duration · attendees) and the body is a markdown editor;
    the toolbar shows a Save action (disabled unless a Connection targets the Calendar). The
    attendee list always ends with a blank ActorList row (react-ui-components): typing `@` opens a
    typeahead against Person names/emails; each completed token (an `@<id>` reference or a
    well-formed email) is committed as an attendee. Toolbar (toolbar idiom): Open (promote from
    companion), Create note, Save (draft only), Delete. Editing resolves the live db object
    (useQuery by id) so inputs stay reactive. Operations are invoked with the calendar db's spaceId
    so their space-affinity services (Database/Feed/Credentials) materialize.
  props:
    subject: Event
    companionTo?: Calendar
  state:
    editable: boolean            # true when the event is draft
    allDay: boolean              # whole-day event (date only); maps to Google start.date/end.date
    endMode: explicit | duration # specify an explicit end DateTime or a duration preset (end = start + d)
  actions:
    open()                       # op:layoutOpen — promote from companion to main view
    save()                       # op:syncDraftEvents (spaceId-scoped) for this event
    delete()                     # op:deleteEvent (spaceId-scoped)
    addAttendee(actor: Actor)    # via the blank ActorList row (Person reference or email)
```

```mdl
component EditMessage
  desc: Compose / reply / forward editor for a DraftMessage.
  props:
    draft: DraftMessage
  actions:
    send()
    saveDraft()
    discard()
  emits:
    onSent(message: Message)
```

## Services

Injected, per-space singletons shared between operations (writers) and companion surfaces (readers)
— both run in the same browser main-thread JS context.

```mdl
service FactStore
  desc: |
    Per-space RDF fact store written by op:analyzeMailbox and read by MailboxFactsCompanion.
    In-memory (browser-safe, non-durable) — facts reset on reload. Durable OPFS/SQLite in a worker is
    the planned follow-up.
    KNOWN GAP: the store's own `cursor`/`setCursor` (an ingest cursor keyed by source DXN) is NOT what
    op:analyzeMailbox uses for its high-water progress — see FeedCursors below. The store's cursor and
    the actual mailbox-analysis cursor are two different, currently-unreconciled mechanisms.
  loading: lazy
  ops:
    putFacts(facts: Fact[])
    query(constraints) → Fact[]
    select(sparql: string) → Fact[]
    cursor(source: string) → string | undefined
    setCursor(source: string, hash: string)
    clear()
```

```mdl
service FeedCursors
  desc: |
    Persisted per-mailbox processing high-water cursor: a real `Cursor` ECHO object (`@dxos/link`,
    `spec.kind: 'feed'`) whose `source` is the mailbox's feed and `target` is the mailbox itself (there
    is no dedicated "fact consumer" object, so the mailbox stands in as the association anchor).
    op:analyzeMailbox finds-or-creates it and advances it as it processes the feed, so re-runs skip
    already-processed messages. NOT modeled as a named service/tag in code — this block documents the
    `findOrCreateFeedCursor` convention in `operations/analyze/analyze-mailbox.ts`, not an injected
    dependency.
    KNOWN GAP: the cursor is durable (survives reload) but FactStore's facts are in-memory (reset on
    reload) — a persisted-cursor-over-empty-store skew across a reload. F-9.4 below currently claims
    this can't happen; it can. Needs a product decision: make facts durable too, or reset the cursor
    alongside a cleared store, or revise F-9.4.
  loading: lazy
  ops:
    findOrCreate(mailbox: Mailbox) → Cursor
    advance(cursor: Cursor, max?: string)
```

## Operations

Effectful operations — mutate persistent state or call external services. Sync operations bind to a
`SyncBinding` (whose Connection owns credentials, whose target is the Mailbox/Calendar); send/create
operations source credentials from a `Connection`.

```mdl
op addMailbox
  desc: Adds a Mailbox to the active space or collection.
  input:
    object: Mailbox
    target: Database | Collection
  output: { id: string, subject: string[], object: Mailbox }
  effects: [echo:write]
```

```mdl
op draftEmail
  desc: Creates a new draft email scoped to a mailbox.
  input:
    subject: string
    to: string
    body: string
    mailbox: Ref<Mailbox>
    replyTo?: Ref<Message>
  output: { newMessageDXN: string }
  effects: [echo:write]
```

```mdl
op draftEmailAndOpen
  desc: draftEmail then opens the draft in EditMessage (UI convenience wrapper).
  input:
    db: Database
    mode?: compose | reply | reply-all | forward
    message?: Message
    subject?: string
    body?: string
    mailbox?: Ref<Mailbox>
  effects: [echo:write]
```

```mdl
op generateReply
  desc: |
    Drafts a reply to a message, grounded on the thread (same normalized subject from the mailbox
    feed) and on facts the space fact store knows about the participants. Fact lookup is advisory
    (degrades to none); the LLM is instructed to hedge non-certain facts and invent nothing.
  input:
    mailbox: Ref<Mailbox>
    message: Message
  output: { subject: string, body: string }
  effects: [echo:read, feed:read, factstore:read, llm]
  requires: [FactStore, AiService]
```

```mdl
op readEmail
  desc: Reads recent messages from a mailbox as a single text payload.
  input:
    mailbox: Ref<Mailbox>
    skip?: number
    limit?: number
  output: { content: string }
  effects: [echo:read, feed:read]
```

```mdl
op renameFilter
  desc: |
    Opens the rename popover for a saved filter (prefilled with its current name); the actual rename
    is applied by the popover's own callback, not synchronously by this op.
  input:
    mailbox: Mailbox
    name: string                # current filter name — both the lookup key and the popover's prefill
    caller?: string              # anchor id for the popover
  effects: [echo:write]
```

```mdl
op classifyEmail
  desc: |
    Picks a tag for a message from the database's tag set (LLM chooses by label match) and applies
    it via a feed relation.
    KNOWN GAP: does not gate on `extractors.threshold` — contradicts req F-6.2 below; always applies
    whatever tag the LLM names, or fails if none matches. Needs a product decision: add the gate back,
    or revise F-6.2 to match current behavior.
  input:
    message: Message
  output: { tagId: string, tagLabel: string } | void
  effects: [echo:read, echo:write, feed:write]
  requires: [AiService]
```

```mdl
op googleMailSync
  desc: |
    Pulls messages from Gmail into the mailbox feed via the binding's cursor.
    KNOWN GAP: no after/before/direction override exists — this and F-3.5's "can be overridden to
    backfill older ranges" describe an unimplemented capability. Walk direction is inferred from the
    cursor (no cursor → backward/newest-first initial pull; cursor → forward incremental) but cannot
    currently be overridden.
  input:
    binding: Ref<SyncBinding>   # connection owns credentials; target is the Mailbox
    userId?: string
    label?: string              # Gmail label; schema annotation says "defaults to inbox" but the
                                 # handler's actual default is 'all' — the two disagree
  output: { newMessages: number }
  effects: [echo:write, feed:write, http]
```

```mdl
op jmapSync
  desc: |
    Pulls messages from a JMAP server (e.g. Fastmail) into the mailbox feed. JMAP mailbox folders map
    to provider Tag objects. Same no-override cursor model as googleMailSync (see its KNOWN GAP note).
  input:
    binding: Ref<SyncBinding>
  output: { newMessages: number }
  effects: [echo:write, feed:write, http]
```

```mdl
op materializeTarget
  desc: |
    Eagerly creates the local Mailbox (materializeGmailTarget / materializeJmapTarget) or Calendar
    (materializeCalendarTarget) bound to a Connection, so a SyncBinding relation can be created
    (relations require both endpoints to exist). Single-target connectors create a fresh target,
    seeding its name from the connection's account.
  input:
    connection: Ref<Connection>
    remoteTarget?: string        # remote id for a multi-target connector's user-selected target
  output: { target: Ref<Mailbox | Calendar> }
  effects: [echo:write]
```

```mdl
op googleCalendarSync
  desc: Pulls events from Google Calendar into the calendar feed (stamps a google.com foreign key on each).
  input:
    binding: Ref<SyncBinding>
    googleCalendarId?: string
    pageSize?: number
    syncBackDays?: number
    syncForwardDays?: number
  output: { newEvents: number }
  effects: [echo:write, feed:write, http]
```

```mdl
op createGoogleCalendarEvent
  desc: Creates a single event on Google Calendar (write counterpart to googleCalendarSync). Requires the calendar.events scope.
  input:
    event: Event
    googleCalendarId: string
    connection: Ref<Connection>
  output: { id: string }        # remote Google event id
  effects: [http]
```

```mdl
op syncDraftEvents
  desc: |
    Pushes draft (local, unsynced) events for a Calendar to Google Calendar (the email draft→send
    analogue). For each: createGoogleCalendarEvent, stamp the google.com foreign key, then (after a
    feed re-sync) remove the local draft so the synced feed copy is the source of truth. When `event`
    is given, only that one is synced. NOTE follow-up: re-anchor an event's note relation onto the
    synced copy before deleting the local draft.
  input:
    calendar: Calendar
    event?: Event               # when omitted, syncs all draft events on the Calendar
  output: { synced: number }
  effects: [echo:write, feed:write, http]
```

```mdl
op deleteEvent
  desc: |
    Deletes a calendar event. A draft (local) event is removed from the db; a synced event is
    deleted on Google Calendar by its foreign key and removed from the calendar feed.
  input:
    calendar: Calendar
    event: Event
  output: { deleted: boolean }
  effects: [echo:write, feed:write, http]
```

```mdl
op deleteEmail
  desc: |
    Deletes an email. A draft (local) message is removed from the db. A synced message is removed by
    foreign key and dropped from the mailbox feed — Gmail-sourced via the Gmail trash (requires
    gmail.modify scope), JMAP-sourced via trashJmapMessage.
  input:
    mailbox: Mailbox
    message: Message
  output: { deleted: boolean }
  effects: [echo:write, feed:write, http]
```

```mdl
op googleContactsSync
  desc: Pulls contacts from a Google contact group into Person objects.
  input:
    binding: Ref<SyncBinding>   # connection owns credentials; remoteId is the contact group
    pageSize?: number
  output: { upserted: number }
  effects: [echo:write, http]
```

```mdl
op gmailSend
  desc: Sends a Message via Gmail using connection credentials.
  input:
    message: Message
    connection: Ref<Connection>
    userId?: string
  output: { id: string, threadId: string, sentTag: { source: string, id: string, label: string } }
  effects: [http]
```

```mdl
op jmapSend
  desc: Sends a Message via a JMAP server using connection credentials.
  input:
    message: Message
    connection: Ref<Connection>
  output: { id: string, threadId: string, sentTag: { source: string, id: string, label: string } }
  effects: [http]
```

```mdl
op extractMessage
  desc: |
    Dispatcher that runs a configured AI extractor over a message and creates/updates structured
    objects, recording provenance via Mailbox.recordExtraction + an ExtractedFrom relation. Delegates
    to per-extractor ops: extractContactFromMessage (Person), extractSummaryFromMessage (a summary
    Markdown.Document), and others registered as ObjectExtractors.
  input:
    source: Message             # live object or immutable feed snapshot
    extractorId?: string        # specific extractor; default runs all enabled
  output:
    extractorId: string
    created: number
    updated: number
    summary?: string
  effects: [echo:write]
  requires: [AiService]
```

```mdl
op extractMailbox
  desc: Runs a selected extractor over every message in a mailbox feed (bounded parallelism).
  input:
    mailbox: Ref<Mailbox>
    extractorId: string
    concurrency?: number        # default 5
  output:
    extractorId: string
    processed: number
    succeeded: number
    failed: number
    created: number
    updated: number
  effects: [echo:write]
  requires: [AiService]
```

```mdl
op analyzeMailbox
  desc: |
    Iterates the mailbox feed and extracts RDF facts from each message into the shared per-space
    FactStore, tracking its own FeedCursors high-water key so re-runs skip processed messages. Facts
    are committed page-atomically. Rendered by MailboxFactsCompanion.
  input:
    mailbox: Ref<Mailbox>
    pageSize?: number           # messages per fact-store commit (default 10)
    model?: string              # extraction model DXN; defaults to the edge Claude model
    provider?: string           # AI provider id (e.g. ollama) for local extraction
    strict?: boolean            # strict structured output; false for weak local models
  output:
    processed: number
    facts: number
  effects: [echo:read, feed:read]
  requires: [AiService, FactStore, FeedCursors]
```

```mdl
op extractContact
  desc: Extracts a Person object from an Actor referenced in a message.
  input:
    db: Database
    actor: Actor
  effects: [echo:write]
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Mailbox

  req F-1.1: Mailbox stores messages in an append-only Feed; never mutates past entries.
  req F-1.2: Messages render newest-first with sender, subject, snippet, and timestamp.
  req F-1.3:
    when: settings.conversations is true
    then: list groups messages by conversation; shows most recent per thread
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Calendar

  req F-2.1: Calendar stores synced events in an append-only Feed.
  req F-2.2: Day and week views render events ordered by start time.
  req F-2.3: CalendarArticle overlays synced (feed) and draft (local) events together on the grid and list.
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Provider Sync

  req F-3.1:
    when: user adds a Google Connection with mail scope and a SyncBinding to a Mailbox
    then: op:googleMailSync runs and populates the mailbox feed

  req F-3.2:
    when: user adds a Google Connection with calendar scope
    then: op:googleCalendarSync runs and populates the calendar feed

  req F-3.3:
    when: user adds a Google Connection with contacts scope
    then: op:googleContactsSync upserts Person objects into the space

  req F-3.4:
    when: user adds a JMAP Connection (e.g. Fastmail) and a SyncBinding to a Mailbox
    then: op:jmapSync runs and populates the mailbox feed

  req F-3.5: Subsequent syncs advance the binding cursor; the walk direction is inferred (no cursor → backward initial pull; cursor → forward incremental) and can be overridden to backfill older ranges.

  req F-3.6: Provider folders/labels are mirrored as Tag objects carrying a provider foreign key (Gmail label / JMAP mailbox).
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Compose & Send

  req F-4.1:
    when: user clicks compose / reply / forward
    then: op:draftEmail (or draftEmailAndOpen) creates a DraftMessage; EditMessage opens for editing

  req F-4.2:
    when: user sends a draft
    then: op:gmailSend or op:jmapSend dispatches via the linked Connection
    errors: [SendFailed, NoConnection]

  req F-4.3:
    when: user clicks delete on a message
    then: op:deleteEmail removes a draft locally, or trashes a synced message on Gmail and drops the feed copy
```

```mdl
feat F-8: Draft Events & Two-way Calendar

  req F-8.1:
    when: user clicks "Create event" on the calendar toolbar
    then: a draft Event is created (db, parented to the Calendar) and focused for editing

  req F-8.2:
    when: an event is draft
    then: EventArticle's header exposes editable title, start/end and body, and the toolbar shows Save

  req F-8.2a:
    when: the user toggles "All day" on a draft
    then: the event is date-only (Event.allDay); it round-trips to Google start.date/end.date (end exclusive)

  req F-8.2b:
    when: the user picks a duration preset instead of an explicit end
    then: endDate = startDate + duration; moving the start preserves the duration

  req F-8.3: User may create multiple draft events offline before saving (e.g. while disconnected).

  req F-8.4:
    when: user clicks Save (per-event in EventArticle, or "Save events to calendar" on the calendar toolbar)
    then: op:syncDraftEvents creates the event(s) on Google Calendar and reconciles into the feed
    errors: [NoConnection, NoCalendarWriteScope]

  req F-8.5:
    when: user clicks delete on a draft event
    then: op:deleteEvent removes it locally; a synced event is deleted on Google and dropped from the feed
```

```mdl
feat F-5: Filters and Labels

  req F-5.1: User can save a named filter expression on the mailbox.
  req F-5.2:
    when: a saved filter is selected
    then: message list shows only matching messages
  req F-5.3:
    when: user renames a saved filter
    then: op:renameFilter updates the filter name in place
```

```mdl
feat F-6: AI Assistance

  req F-6.1: Plugin contributes an Inbox skill with read / draft / classify / sync / extract tools.
  req F-6.2:
    when: agent calls op:classifyEmail on a message
    then: best-matching tag is applied; no tag applied below extractors.threshold

  req F-6.3:
    when: agent calls op:extractMessage on a confirmation email
    then: structured objects (e.g. Trip segments) are created or updated

  req F-6.4:
    when: the user clicks "AI Reply" in the message toolbar
    then: op:generateReply drafts a grounded reply body and a prefilled reply draft opens

  req F-6.5:
    when: the user clicks "Generate" in the reply-draft toolbar
    then: op:generateReply fills the open draft's body from the message it replies to
```

```mdl
feat F-7: Related Content

  req F-7.1:
    when: a message is selected
    then: related contacts, events, and thread messages are shown alongside the reading pane

  req F-7.2:
    when: user clicks a related contact
    then: navigation opens the Person object
```

```mdl
feat F-9: Fact Enrichment

  req F-9.1:
    when: op:analyzeMailbox runs over a mailbox feed
    then: RDF facts are extracted per message into the shared per-space FactStore

  req F-9.2: op:analyzeMailbox advances a FeedCursors high-water key so re-runs skip already-processed messages.

  req F-9.3:
    when: a Mailbox is open
    then: MailboxFactsCompanion renders the mailbox's extracted facts via FactViewer

  req F-9.4: |
    FactStore facts are in-memory (reset on reload); FeedCursors' cursor is durable (survives reload)
    — see FeedCursors' KNOWN GAP note for the resulting skew and the open product decision. Durable
    worker-hosted fact storage is a planned follow-up.
```

```mdl
feat F-10: Starring & Reading Preferences

  req F-10.1:
    when: user stars a message or event
    then: the well-known "starred" Tag is applied via the container's TagIndex (toggles off on re-star)

  req F-10.2:
    when: settings.loadRemoteImages is false (default)
    then: remote images in a message body are shown as plain links, not fetched (anti-tracking)
```

```mdl
feat F-11: Responsiveness & Sync Integrity

  desc: |
    Perceived performance and correctness guarantees for the mailbox experience. Latency budgets are
    p95, measured from user action (or surface mount) to first meaningful paint of the requested
    content, and must hold WHILE a background sync is running. Each budget has two levels: a target
    (the number to design for) and a ceiling (the max acceptable). A scenario fails above the ceiling,
    and is not yet meeting goal until it reaches the target.

  req F-11.1:
    when: an initial sync is running (first-time or backfill)
    then: the inbox remains interactive — the user can scroll, select messages, open threads, compose, and change filters; sync progress is non-blocking

  req F-11.2:
    when: a previously set-up mailbox is (re)loaded and its data query has not yet resolved
    then: the mailbox does not render an empty state; it shows already-persisted/cached messages (or a skeleton over them), never a false "no messages" view

  req F-11.3:
    when: a mailbox is opened
    then: the first page of messages is painted within 400ms (p95 ceiling); target 100ms

  req F-11.4:
    when: an email thread is selected
    then: the thread renders in the companion within 400ms (p95 ceiling), including while a sync is running; target 100ms

  req F-11.5:
    when: mail sync runs (any provider, any number of concurrent/overlapping runs)
    then: it is idempotent — a message already in the mailbox feed is never duplicated
    note: |
      Intended implementation: run all sync on edge with a lock around the mailbox so concurrent
      syncs serialize on a single writer. That mechanism is OUT OF SCOPE for the current session;
      this requirement records the guarantee the design must ultimately satisfy. Feed-level dedup by
      foreign key / message id is the interim backstop.
```

## Acceptance

Each scenario is tagged with the harness tier(s) that enforce it (`unit`, `storybook`,
`agent-e2e`, `browser-e2e`, `bench`, `live`); enforcing tests carry the `T-#` id in their name.
See `docs/superpowers/plans/2026-07-12-inbox-test-plan.md` for the tier definitions and the
spec↔suite sync convention.

```mdl
test T-1: Sync Gmail into mailbox
  given: a Mailbox with a SyncBinding to a Google Connection with valid credentials
  when: op:googleMailSync runs
  then:
    - newMessages > 0 on first run
    - Mailbox.feed contains Message entries ordered by received-at
  tags: [unit, live]
```

```mdl
test T-2: Save and apply filter
  given: Mailbox open with > 1 messages, including one from alice@example.com
  when: user saves filter "from:alice@example.com" and selects it
  then:
    - message list shows only messages matching the filter
  tags: [unit, browser-e2e]
```

```mdl
test T-3: Draft and send reply
  given: a Message is selected in the mailbox
  when: user clicks reply, edits the body, and sends
  then:
    - op:draftEmail creates a DraftMessage with replyTo set
    - op:gmailSend (or op:jmapSend) dispatches via the linked Connection
    - sent message appears in the mailbox feed on next sync
  tags: [unit, live]
```

```mdl
test T-4: Classify message
  given: a Message and a tag set with confidence threshold 0.7
  when: op:classifyEmail runs
  then:
    - if best tag confidence ≥ 0.7, tag applied
    - otherwise no tag applied
  tags: [unit, agent-e2e]
```

```mdl
test T-5: Extract confirmation
  given: a flight booking confirmation email
  when: op:extractMessage runs with the trip extractor enabled
  then:
    - Trip segment objects created or updated
    - extractMessage output reports created/updated counts
  tags: [unit]
```

```mdl
test T-6: Create and save a draft event
  given: a Calendar linked to a Google Connection with calendar.events scope
  when: user clicks "Create event", edits the title and date, then clicks Save
  then:
    - a draft Event (parented to the Calendar, no google.com foreign key) is created and focused
    - it is overlaid on the calendar grid and event list before saving
    - op:syncDraftEvents calls op:createGoogleCalendarEvent and the event lands in the calendar feed
    - the local draft Event is removed after reconciliation
  tags: [live, browser-e2e]
```

```mdl
test T-7: Delete event and email
  given: a synced Event and a synced Message
  when: user clicks delete in EventArticle and in MessageArticle
  then:
    - op:deleteEvent deletes the event on Google Calendar and removes it from the calendar feed
    - op:deleteEmail trashes the message on Gmail and removes it from the mailbox feed
    - a draft event / draft message would instead be removed locally only
  tags: [unit, live]
```

```mdl
test T-8: Sync JMAP into mailbox
  given: a Mailbox with a SyncBinding to a JMAP Connection (e.g. Fastmail) with valid credentials
  when: op:jmapSync runs
  then:
    - newMessages > 0 on first run
    - JMAP mailbox folders are represented as provider Tag objects
  tags: [unit, live]
```

```mdl
test T-9: Enrich mailbox into fact store
  given: a Mailbox feed with N messages and an available AiService
  when: op:analyzeMailbox runs, then runs a second time in the same session
  then:
    - first run: facts > 0 in the FactStore; processed === N
    - second run: processed === 0 (FeedCursors high-water skip); fact count unchanged
    - MailboxFactsCompanion renders the extracted facts
  tags: [unit, storybook]
```

```mdl
test T-10: Interactive during initial sync
  given: a set-up Mailbox with an initial sync in progress
  when: the user scrolls, selects a message, opens a thread, and changes the filter
  then:
    - every interaction responds; no interaction is blocked waiting on sync
  tags: [performance, browser-e2e]
```

```mdl
test T-11: No empty state on reload
  given: a Mailbox previously synced with persisted messages
  when: the mailbox is reloaded and its data query has not yet resolved
  then:
    - the persisted messages (or a skeleton over them) are shown
    - a "no messages" empty state is never shown while the query is pending
  tags: [performance, storybook, browser-e2e]
```

```mdl
test T-12: Latency budgets
  given: a set-up Mailbox (measured at p95, including while a sync is running)
  when: the mailbox is opened, then an email thread is selected
  then:
    - first page of messages painted within 400ms (target 100ms)
    - selected thread rendered in the companion within 400ms (target 100ms)
  tags: [performance, bench, browser-e2e]
```

```mdl
test T-13: Idempotent sync
  given: a Mailbox with messages already in its feed
  when: sync runs again (and when two syncs overlap)
  then:
    - no message is duplicated in the mailbox feed
  tags: [correctness, unit, live]
```

---

## Appendix: Extension Definitions

```mdl
ext type
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0
  desc: A named data structure with typed fields and optional literals.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    fields?: FieldMap
    literals?: UnionList
    extends?: TypeRef[]
```

```mdl
ext feat
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0
  desc: A named feature grouping one or more requirements.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    req: RequirementList
  nesting: self
```

```mdl
ext test
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0
  desc: An acceptance scenario expressed as given / when / then steps.
  fields:
    given?: Step | Step[]
    when?: Step | Step[]
    then: Step | Step[]
    tags?: TagList
```

```mdl
ext component
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0
  desc: A UI component with props, internal state, slots, actions, and events.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    props?: FieldMap
    state?: FieldMap
    slots?: FieldMap
    actions?: ActionMap
    emits?: EventMap
    layout?: CodeBlock
```

```mdl
ext service
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0
  desc: An external or system-level dependency providing named operations.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    loading?: eager | lazy
    ops?: OpMap
    errors?: ErrorMap
    note?: Prose
```

```mdl
ext op
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0
  desc: |
    A named operation with typed inputs, outputs, and declared errors.
    Pure ops have no effects or requires. Effectful ops declare both.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    input?: FieldMap
    output?: TypeExpr
    errors?: ErrorMap
    effects?: EffectList
    requires?: ServiceList
    note?: Prose
```
